biography.content:
I am a computational biomedicine researcher, with a solid computer science and biomedical engineering research background I acquired in academy and industry over 10 years in Romania, Ireland (where I obtained my PhD in 2014), France and Luxembourg. I have experience in translational projects including the Cardiovascular HeartMed ERA-Net Cofund in Personalised Medicine project, the large-scale IMI eTRIKS translational research project and the Cancer Epigenetics-focused CIESCI ERA-Net Complexity project. I was awarded with an IMI FAIRplus Fellowship (June 2021- May 2022), where I focused on using RDA indicators for assessing FAIRness (FAIR principles: Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) in several translational projects and for the Molecular Interaction NEtwoRk VisuAlization (MINERVA) platform. 

I am a coordinator of the ISCB Translational Medicine Informatics community and of the Metabolism Regulation Maps community project. I am appointed as an editor for the Systems Biology Graphical Notation (SBGN) standard (2021-2023), which is one of the core COmputational Modeling in BIology NEtwork (COMBINE) standards. I am committed to promote open science and open code as well as reproducible research. I am currently a coordinator an European Open Science Cloud (EOSC) Future - funded project on using FAIR indicators for COMBINE models (October 2022 - March 2023). I am also an alumni of the University of Luxembourg Leadership Academy (ULLA) training (October 2021 - December 2021) on key leadership principles.

Particular areas of expertise include computational modelling of biomedical complex systems, large-scale data management (FAIRification, integration, analysis), development of multiscale models in cancer, exploration of the role of epigenetics in cancer, use of machine learning techniques in biomedical networks, use of systems biology standards.
